 offering certainly looks ridiculously impressive. At a 6k starting price plus the 5k pro display (sold separately), this is certainly out of range for any normal consumer. But hey, that‚Äôs why its a PRO device!<li><p>There was a pretty hilarious bit by Craig Federighi as he showed off mail and other apps embedded in iTunes (as a joke) right before he explains how iTunes functionality has in-fact now been pulled apart into several different apps. <strong>RIP iTunes: 2001-2019</strong><li><p>Catalyst (formerly known as Marzipan) should bring a lot of awesome capabilities to the Mac by way of iPad apps. The iPad has a rich ecosystem of apps and many that I would love to see on the Mac.</ul><p>Overall, a pretty solid showing by Apple. I‚Äôm excited to try it all out in the near future! (with the exception of the Mac Pro as it‚Äôs definitely out of the price and power range for me personally).</div></article><hr class="fin"><div id="poststats" class="containbox" style="margin: auto;"> <span class="time"><i class="ph ph-calendar-dot"></i> Published: <span class="dt-published">June 3, 2019</span></span> <a class="u-url u-uid" href></a><br> <span class='time'><i class="ph ph-calendar-dot"></i> Updated: <span class="dt-updated">June 20, 2019</span></span><br/> <span class="categories"><i class="ph ph-tag"></i> Tags: <span class="primarybg" style="border-radius:15px;padding:0px 5px 0px 5px;"><a class="p-category" href="/tags?tag=apple">#apple</a></span> <span class="primarybg" style="border-radius:15px;padding:0px 5px 0px 5px;"><a class="p-category" href="/tags?tag=technology">#technology</a></span> </span><br/> <span class="time"><i class="ph ph-pencil"></i> Word count: 1209</span> <span class="p-summary" style="display:none;">My thoughts on WWDC 2019.</span></div><br/><div class="PageNavigation"> <a class="prev" style="margin-right: 2em;" href="/mac-tools#title">&laquo; Mac Tools</a><div style="float:right;"><a class="next" href="/infosec-tools#title" style="margin-right: